 <datafield tag="245" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
  <subfield code="a">Evolution of magnetic field fluctuations in two-dimensional chaotic flow</subfield>
  <subfield code="9">IOP</subfield>
 </datafield>
 <datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
  <subfield code="a">The two-point correlation tensor of small-scale fluctuations of magnetic field $\boldsymbol{B}$ in a two-dimensional chaotic flow is studied. The analytic approach is developed in the framework of the Kraichnan–Kazantsev model. It is shown that the growth of the field fluctuations takes place in an essentially resistive regime and stops at large times in accordance with the so-called anti-dynamo theorems. The value of $\boldsymbol{B}^{{2}}$ is enhanced in the course of the evolution by the magnetic Prandtl number.</subfield>
  <subfield code="9">IOP</subfield>
 </datafield>
